summary: This is an FBI property receipt form documenting the collection/seizure or receipt of items related to the Epstein case. The form includes a description of items, likely evidence, and is subject to a protective order restricting certain paragraphs.
keyFacts: The document is an FBI property receipt (Form 95) used to document the collection, seizure, receipt, return, or release of items.
The receipt is related to the Epstein case, as indicated by the case reference and the EFTA document numbers.
The document is subject to a protective order that restricts paragraphs 7, 8, 9, 10, 15, and 17, indicating sensitive or confidential information.
The description of the item(s) is partially illegible but appears to reference a 'Sista' and 'Flo JoNre.se', which may be codenames, nicknames, or garbled text for evidence items.
The receipt was executed on June 1, 2021, as indicated by the date stamp '6/1/2021'.
